Panel Number: diagrams of panel locations (up to date as far as I know) can be found here
Cable length (cm): Signal cables -- pwr cables have different lengths
LTB Number-Channel: LTB Number = RAT Box Number. Matches PB Number-Channel. comes from this spreadsheet SMA-LG tabs
RB Number-Channel: RB Numbers are based on BOARD ID (not RAT). RAT-RB connection comes from this spreadsheet SMA-HG tabs, but need to determine actual RB IDs in the positions RB1 and RB2 and use this diagram to get RB channel.  should now be correct
PB Number-Channel: PB Number = BOARD ID (not RAT). connection comes from this spreadsheet, but need to know actual PB ID in the RAT for proper lookup table to be used.
PB controlled by which RB: PB is controlled by the RB closest to it in the stack (RB2 from this diagram)
LTB controlled by which RB: LTB is controlled by the RB closest to it in the stack (RB1 from this diagram)
Panel Type: cube top, cube side, cortina, umbrella, corner, cube bottom
RB Harting connection split: Y-split for RB Harting cable, A || B "A" is RB1/closer to LTB. "B" is RB2/closer to the PB
